verses.roman:
haite haite haila garbha trayodaśa māsa
tathāpi bhūmiṣṭha nahe,--miśrera haila trāsa

synonyms: haite haite—thus becoming; haila—it so became; garbha—pregnancy; trayodaśa—thirteenth; māsa—month; tathāpi—still; bhūmiṣṭha—delivery; nahe—there was no sign; miśrera—of Jagannātha Miśra; haila—became; trāsa—apprehension.
translation: In this way the pregnancy approached its thirteenth month, but still there was no sign of the delivery of the child. Thus Jagannātha Miśra became greatly apprehensive.
